canonical:
  title: 崔春軒壺矢銘
  author: 李齊賢
  language: lzh
  text: 壺虛其心矢且其理匪直匪虛匪壺匪矢必愼必中若虞張機詭遇獲十勝不償譏勿激而墜勿旋而倚君子之嬉君子之規
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 崔春軒壺矢銘
  author: 李齊賢
  language: lzh
  text: 壺虛其心。矢且其理。匪直匪虛。匪壺匪矢。必愼必中。若虞張機。詭遇獲十。勝不償譏。勿激而墜。勿旋而倚。君子之嬉。君子之規。
korean:
  title: 최춘헌 호시 명
  author: 이제현
  language: kor
  text: 병은 그 속이 비었으며 화살은 그 생리가 곧다. 곧은 것이 아니고 빈 것이 아니면 병도 아니요 화살도 아니다. 반드시 조심하여 반드시 맞추어서 사냥꾼이 틀을 놓은 것같이 하라. 짐승을 속여서 열 마리를 잡아도 이긴 것이 기롱을 갚지 못한다. 세게 던지다가 떨어뜨리지도 말고 돌려 넣어려고 비뚤어지게 말지어다. 군자의 놀이라, 군자의 규모로다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0520_040_0160&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Inscription on Choe Chun-heon's Vessel and Arrow
  author: Lee Che-hyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The vessel empties its heart,
    The arrow straightens its path.
    Without straightness, without emptiness—
    Neither vessel nor arrow remains.

    Be ever cautious, ever true,
    Like the hunter's careful aim.
    Ten beasts deceived and caught,
    Yet victory cannot repay the mockery.

    Let not force make it fall,
    Let not turning make it lean.
    This is the gentleman's play,
    The gentleman's measure and rule.
  footnotes:
    - A mingwen (銘文), or inscription, was traditionally written to commemorate or instruct on the proper use of an object. This piece celebrates both the physical properties of a vessel and arrow as well as their metaphorical significance for cultivated virtue.
    - The reference to the hunter and the number ten suggests both skill in archery and the Confucian principle that martial prowess must be tempered by moral restraint.
    - The 'gentleman' (君子) references the Confucian ideal of the cultivated person whose actions embody both discipline and grace.
